<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="392" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,972,2043]" pageId="1" pageNumber="392">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1044,1070]" pageId="1" pageNumber="392">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The characters shared by 
<taxonomicName authority="(Schreber)" baseAuthorityName="Schreber" baseAuthorityYear="1759" box="[615,865,1044,1071]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Lestica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="392" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="clypeata">
<emphasis box="[615,739,1044,1070]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="392">L. clypeata</emphasis>
(Schreber)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[919,1113,1044,1070]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Lestica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="392" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="robustispinosa">
<emphasis box="[919,1113,1044,1070]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="392">L. robustispinosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are as follows: mandible tridentate at apex, inner side of mandible with one tooth; middle lobe of clypeus narrow, conspicuously elevated, free margin of clypeus truncate; pronotum conspicuously acute laterally; ratio scape length: IODm = 3:2; outer surface of fore femur with U-shaped carina; gastral terga not constricted; pygidial plate conspicuously narrowed and gutterlike.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,972,2043]" pageId="1" pageNumber="392">
The new species clearly differs from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Schreber" baseAuthorityYear="1759" box="[624,750,1224,1250]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Lestica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="392" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="clypeata">
<emphasis box="[624,750,1224,1250]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="392">L. clypeata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the following characters: mesosternum with very sparse, deep punctures submedially, interspaces much larger than puncture diameter, mesosternum side with irregular, deep, huge punctures, some punctures contiguous, and some with interspaces (
<figureCitation box="[957,1036,1296,1322]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1495,1519]" captionTargetBox="[161,1431,306,1459]" captionTargetId="figure-99@2.[151,1436,303,1471]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Lestica robustispinosa Yue &amp; Ma, sp. nov., Holotype ♀. a. Habitus, dorsal view. b. Head, frontal view. c. Head, dorsal view. d. Mesosoma, dorsal view. e. Mesosternum. f. Hind leg. g. Fore leg. h. Fore wing. i. Pygidial plate, dorsal view. j. Metasoma, dorsal view. Scale bar = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6079220" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6079220/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="392">Fig. 1e</figureCitation>
); processes on outer surface of hind tibia conspicuous, continually connected, with sturdy spine (
<figureCitation box="[836,915,1332,1359]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1495,1519]" captionTargetBox="[161,1431,306,1459]" captionTargetId="figure-99@2.[151,1436,303,1471]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Lestica robustispinosa Yue &amp; Ma, sp. nov., Holotype ♀. a. Habitus, dorsal view. b. Head, frontal view. c. Head, dorsal view. d. Mesosoma, dorsal view. e. Mesosternum. f. Hind leg. g. Fore leg. h. Fore wing. i. Pygidial plate, dorsal view. j. Metasoma, dorsal view. Scale bar = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6079220" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6079220/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="392">Fig. 1f</figureCitation>
); antero-lateral angle of pronotal collar small, acutely pointed on each side (
<figureCitation box="[484,566,1368,1395]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1495,1519]" captionTargetBox="[161,1431,306,1459]" captionTargetId="figure-99@2.[151,1436,303,1471]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Lestica robustispinosa Yue &amp; Ma, sp. nov., Holotype ♀. a. Habitus, dorsal view. b. Head, frontal view. c. Head, dorsal view. d. Mesosoma, dorsal view. e. Mesosternum. f. Hind leg. g. Fore leg. h. Fore wing. i. Pygidial plate, dorsal view. j. Metasoma, dorsal view. Scale bar = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6079220" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6079220/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="392">Fig. 1d</figureCitation>
); gastral terga I-V with small lateral spot on each side (
<figureCitation box="[1189,1264,1368,1395]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1495,1519]" captionTargetBox="[161,1431,306,1459]" captionTargetId="figure-99@2.[151,1436,303,1471]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Lestica robustispinosa Yue &amp; Ma, sp. nov., Holotype ♀. a. Habitus, dorsal view. b. Head, frontal view. c. Head, dorsal view. d. Mesosoma, dorsal view. e. Mesosternum. f. Hind leg. g. Fore leg. h. Fore wing. i. Pygidial plate, dorsal view. j. Metasoma, dorsal view. Scale bar = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6079220" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6079220/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="392">Fig. 1j</figureCitation>
); pronotal lobe posteriorly yellow; outer ventral surface of hind tibia (except black spot) yellow, inner side yellowish brown (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1495,1519]" captionTargetBox="[161,1431,306,1459]" captionTargetId="figure-99@2.[151,1436,303,1471]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Lestica robustispinosa Yue &amp; Ma, sp. nov., Holotype ♀. a. Habitus, dorsal view. b. Head, frontal view. c. Head, dorsal view. d. Mesosoma, dorsal view. e. Mesosternum. f. Hind leg. g. Fore leg. h. Fore wing. i. Pygidial plate, dorsal view. j. Metasoma, dorsal view. Scale bar = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6079220" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6079220/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="392">Fig. 1f</figureCitation>
); fore and mid femora black (
<figureCitation box="[525,609,1440,1466]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1495,1519]" captionTargetBox="[161,1431,306,1459]" captionTargetId="figure-99@2.[151,1436,303,1471]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Lestica robustispinosa Yue &amp; Ma, sp. nov., Holotype ♀. a. Habitus, dorsal view. b. Head, frontal view. c. Head, dorsal view. d. Mesosoma, dorsal view. e. Mesosternum. f. Hind leg. g. Fore leg. h. Fore wing. i. Pygidial plate, dorsal view. j. Metasoma, dorsal view. Scale bar = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6079220" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6079220/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="392">
Fig. 
<quantity box="[579,609,1440,1466]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="1.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="392" unit="g" value="1.0">1g</quantity>
</figureCitation>
). In 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Schreber" baseAuthorityYear="1759" box="[665,792,1440,1466]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Lestica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="392" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="clypeata">
<emphasis box="[665,792,1440,1466]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="392">L. clypeata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, mesosternum with dense, coarse punctures, interspaces between punctures hardly visible; outer surface of hind tibia with spines, spines borne on relatively small processes, processes separated; antero-lateral angle of pronotal collar with acutely sharper and long projection on each side; gastral terga I-III with large lateral spots, terga IV-V with stripe spots; pronotal lobe entirely yellow; hind tibia yellow; fore and mid femora yellow beneath and apically.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="394" pageId="1" pageNumber="392" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,972,2043]" pageId="1" pageNumber="392">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1620,1646]" pageId="1" pageNumber="392">Description.</emphasis>
Female (
<figureCitation box="[447,525,1620,1646]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1495,1519]" captionTargetBox="[161,1431,306,1459]" captionTargetId="figure-99@2.[151,1436,303,1471]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Lestica robustispinosa Yue &amp; Ma, sp. nov., Holotype ♀. a. Habitus, dorsal view. b. Head, frontal view. c. Head, dorsal view. d. Mesosoma, dorsal view. e. Mesosternum. f. Hind leg. g. Fore leg. h. Fore wing. i. Pygidial plate, dorsal view. j. Metasoma, dorsal view. Scale bar = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6079220" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6079220/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="392">Fig. 1a</figureCitation>
). Body length 11.0 mm. Black; yellow are: outer surface of scape (
<figureCitation box="[1261,1341,1620,1647]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1495,1519]" captionTargetBox="[161,1431,306,1459]" captionTargetId="figure-99@2.[151,1436,303,1471]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Lestica robustispinosa Yue &amp; Ma, sp. nov., Holotype ♀. a. Habitus, dorsal view. b. Head, frontal view. c. Head, dorsal view. d. Mesosoma, dorsal view. e. Mesosternum. f. Hind leg. g. Fore leg. h. Fore wing. i. Pygidial plate, dorsal view. j. Metasoma, dorsal view. Scale bar = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6079220" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6079220/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="392">Fig. 1b</figureCitation>
), pronotal lobe posteriorly, fore femur apically, outer surface of fore tibia, ventral surface of fore tarsomere I, mid tarsomere I basally, outer surface of hind tibia (except black spot submedially), small lateral spots on gastral terga I-V (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1495,1519]" captionTargetBox="[161,1431,306,1459]" captionTargetId="figure-99@2.[151,1436,303,1471]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Lestica robustispinosa Yue &amp; Ma, sp. nov., Holotype ♀. a. Habitus, dorsal view. b. Head, frontal view. c. Head, dorsal view. d. Mesosoma, dorsal view. e. Mesosternum. f. Hind leg. g. Fore leg. h. Fore wing. i. Pygidial plate, dorsal view. j. Metasoma, dorsal view. Scale bar = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6079220" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6079220/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="392">Fig. 1j</figureCitation>
); yellowish brown are: inner surface of fore tibia, fore tarsomere I (except outer ventral surface), mid tarsomere I largely, fore and mid tarsomeres II-V, inner surface of hind tibia, and hind tarsomere I basally; reddish brown are: tegula, mid and hind femora apically, and hind tarsus. Clypeus and lower inner eye margin with dense, appressed, silvery setae; lower gena and mesopleuron with sparse, silvery setae; posterior margin of gastral sterna II-V with long, sparse, brown setae; pygidial plate laterally with dense, long, brown setae (
<figureCitation box="[1055,1130,1872,1899]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1495,1519]" captionTargetBox="[161,1431,306,1459]" captionTargetId="figure-99@2.[151,1436,303,1471]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Lestica robustispinosa Yue &amp; Ma, sp. nov., Holotype ♀. a. Habitus, dorsal view. b. Head, frontal view. c. Head, dorsal view. d. Mesosoma, dorsal view. e. Mesosternum. f. Hind leg. g. Fore leg. h. Fore wing. i. Pygidial plate, dorsal view. j. Metasoma, dorsal view. Scale bar = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6079220" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6079220/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="392">Fig. 1i</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,972,2043]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1436,151,285]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="393" pageId="1" pageNumber="392">
<emphasis box="[199,260,1908,1934]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="392">Head</emphasis>
. Mandible tridentate at apex, inner side of mandible with one tooth; middle lobe of clypeus narrow, conspicuously elevated, free margin of clypeus truncate, slightly emarginated medially, laterally with one tooth on each side (
<figureCitation box="[212,293,1980,2007]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1495,1519]" captionTargetBox="[161,1431,306,1459]" captionTargetId="figure-99@2.[151,1436,303,1471]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Lestica robustispinosa Yue &amp; Ma, sp. nov., Holotype ♀. a. Habitus, dorsal view. b. Head, frontal view. c. Head, dorsal view. d. Mesosoma, dorsal view. e. Mesosternum. f. Hind leg. g. Fore leg. h. Fore wing. i. Pygidial plate, dorsal view. j. Metasoma, dorsal view. Scale bar = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6079220" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6079220/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="392">Fig. 1b</figureCitation>
); orbital fovea long and narrow, 6 × as long as widest part (
<figureCitation box="[960,1040,1980,2006]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1495,1519]" captionTargetBox="[161,1431,306,1459]" captionTargetId="figure-99@2.[151,1436,303,1471]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Lestica robustispinosa Yue &amp; Ma, sp. nov., Holotype ♀. a. Habitus, dorsal view. b. Head, frontal view. c. Head, dorsal view. d. Mesosoma, dorsal view. e. Mesosternum. f. Hind leg. g. Fore leg. h. Fore wing. i. Pygidial plate, dorsal view. j. Metasoma, dorsal view. Scale bar = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6079220" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6079220/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="392">Fig. 1c</figureCitation>
); relative length of antennal flagellomere I: flagellomere II: flagellomere III = 13:13:12, last flagellomere 2 × as long as wide; ratio of scape length: IODm = 3:2; OOD: POD: OCD = 10:9:24; upper frons with dense, deep, midsize to huge punctures ca. 0.0–2 × diameters apart; vertex with dense, midsize to large punctures ca. 0.0–1.5 × diameters apart; gena shiny, with dense, small to midsize punctures ca. 1–2 × diameters apart dorsally, and with sparse, small to midsize punctures ca. 0.2–5 × diameters apart ventrally; occipital carina not reaching hypostomal carina.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6079220" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6079220" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6079220/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="393" startId="2.[151,250,1495,1519]" targetBox="[161,1431,306,1459]" targetPageId="2">
