<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="394" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,151,789]" pageId="3" pageNumber="394">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,691,717]" pageId="3" pageNumber="394">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species’ name, 
<taxonomicName box="[563,727,691,717]" class="Insecta" family="Crabronidae" genus="Lestica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="394" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="robustispinosa">
<emphasis box="[563,727,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="394">robustispinosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, is derived from the Latin stem 
<emphasis box="[1091,1162,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="394">robust</emphasis>
- (=stout, strong, sturdy) and the Latin word 
<emphasis box="[369,465,727,752]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="394">spinosus</emphasis>
, referring to the outer surface of hind tibia with sturdy spines, which is one of the main diagnostic characters of this species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
